==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: feudal
<hw>feu"dal</hw> <pr>(f⟦umac⟧"d⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>f⟦eacute⟧odal</ets>, or LL. <ets>feudalis</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Of or pertaining to feuds, fiefs, or fees; <as>as, <ex>feudal</ex>
rights or services; <ex>feudal</ex> tenures.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Consisting of, or founded upon, feuds or fiefs;
embracing tenures by military services; <as>as, the <ex>feudal</ex>
system</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feudalism</ent>⟦br⟧
